Obstructionism Doesn't Excuse Obamacare Site's Difficulties, Or Drone Attacks
The memory of Obama's 2008 campaign is a sad reminder of what could have happened
Nathaniel P. Morris is a 2nd year medical student at Harvard School of Medicine.
I am reading an awfully sad book these days.
This is a book that I thought would encourage me during the sluggish second year of medicine and give me hope again.
